I now have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me compile the full implementation plan.

---

## Implementation Plan: `@prisma/generator-rest-client`

### Architecture Overview

The package follows the same shape as `@prisma/generator-helper` and `@prisma/adapter-pg`. The build system uses `adapterConfig` from `helpers/compile/configs.ts` (CJS + ESM bundles from `src/index.ts`). Code generation uses template strings throughout (not `@prisma/ts-builders`) because the CRUD method bodies contain runtime fetch logic that `ts-builders` cannot emit. `@prisma/ts-builders` is listed as a dependency in the spec but since the requirement says "use Option 2 — pure template strings," it should be removed from dependencies to avoid a spurious import; however, the spec requires it in `dependencies`, so it is kept and may be used for purely type-level helper functions in future extensions.

---

### Step 1 — `packages/generator-rest-client/package.json`

The `sourceFilePath` field in `GeneratorConfig` and the absence of a `prepublishOnly` in some packages means we follow `generator-helper` exactly. Note: `generator-helper` has no `module` or `exports` field. Since the spec requires both, follow `@prisma/generator` as the reference.

```json
{
  "name": "@prisma/generator-rest-client",
  "version": "0.0.0",
  "description": "Prisma generator that emits a typed TypeScript REST API client",
  "main": "dist/index.js",
  "module": "dist/index.mjs",
  "types": "dist/index.d.ts",
  "exports": {
    ".": {
      "require": {
        "types": "./dist/index.d.ts",
        "default": "./dist/index.js"
      },
      "import": {
        "types": "./dist/index.d.ts",
        "default": "./dist/index.mjs"
      }
    }
  },
  "repository": {
    "type": "git",
    "url": "https://github.com/prisma/prisma.git",
    "directory": "packages/generator-rest-client"
  },
  "license": "Apache-2.0",
  "scripts": {
    "dev": "DEV=true tsx helpers/build.ts",
    "build": "tsx helpers/build.ts",
    "test": "vitest run",
    "prepublishOnly": "pnpm run build"
  },
  "files": [
    "dist",
    "README.md"
  ],
  "sideEffects": false,
  "dependencies": {
    "@prisma/dmmf": "workspace:*",
    "@prisma/generator": "workspace:*",
    "@prisma/generator-helper": "workspace:*",
    "@prisma/ts-builders": "workspace:*"
  },
  "devDependencies": {
    "@types/node": "~20.19.24",
    "typescript": "5.4.5"
  }
}
```

Key decision: `@prisma/generator-helper` is a `dependency` (not `devDependency`) because the built output re-exports `generatorHandler` which is needed at runtime by the generator binary. This matches how community generators consume the package.

---

### Step 2 — `packages/generator-rest-client/tsconfig.json`

```json
{ "extends": "../../tsconfig.json", "include": ["./**/*"] }
```

Matches `packages/generator-helper/tsconfig.json` exactly.

---

### Step 3 — `packages/generator-rest-client/tsconfig.build.json`

```json
{
  "extends": "../../tsconfig.build.regular.json",
  "compilerOptions": { "outDir": "dist", "rootDir": "src" },
  "include": ["src"]
}
```

Uses `outDir: "dist"` (not `"declaration"` as seen in `adapter-pg`) because the build system uses `adapterConfig` which writes to `dist/` via esbuild, not `tsc`. The `rootDir` is needed so that declaration files are emitted under `dist/` without an extra `src/` subdirectory level.

---

### Step 4 — `packages/generator-rest-client/helpers/build.ts`

```ts
