1. **Models with no scalar fields at all**: The generated interfaces will have empty bodies (`{}`). The TypeScript compiler accepts this as `interface Foo {}` which is a valid empty interface. The client class will still be generated but `WhereUniqueInput` will be empty — the fallback in `model-types.ts` produces `{}` which is acceptable.

