## Edge Cases to Handle During Implementation

| Case | Handling |
|---|---|
| Model with no `@id` or `@unique` fields | `WhereUniqueInput` is empty `{}` — still emitted |
| All fields are auto-generated | `CreateInput` is empty `{}` — still valid |
| Field has `@default(value)` (static, not function) | Stays in `CreateInput` but marked optional |
| Nullable list field (`String[]?`) | Type becomes `string[] \| null` |
| Enum field (`kind === 'enum'`) | Type name passed through; user must import enums separately |
| Model with relation-only referencing fields (`isReadOnly: true`) | `isReadOnly` fields excluded from `CreateInput`/`UpdateInput` (FK backing fields are auto-managed) |
| `updatedAt` field (`isUpdatedAt: true`) | Treated same as auto fields — excluded from Create/UpdateInput |
